last_replies.com:
There is too much music, but the answer isn't to stop making music.

The problem is that now there is so much music out there, that the best stuff is buried under a lot of mediocrity on the internet. Some good things get highlighted, but so do a lot of mediocre things, and it's obvious there's a lot that's getting lost in the shuffle.

The answer isn't to discourage people from making music, or to tell people to only make music if they're good, because that wouldn't actually weed out the untalented. It would only weed out the unconfident. There are lots of great artists who have not yet honed themselves, or who lack confidence. So we would lose their voices, while amplifying the untalented, overconfident ones.
